#compdef jjui
# Documentation: source-direct extraction from upstream
# idursun/jjui cmd/jjui/main.go —
#   `var` block at lines 43-51 (7 flag-state variables)
#   `init()` at lines 53-69 (10 flag.{String,Int,Bool}Var calls
#     registering 7 unique options, 3 with dual short+long
#     forms)
#   `run()` at lines 86-145 (dispatch logic + positional
#     location handling)
# Reference accessed: 2026-05-30 via gh api.
#
# jjui is the **TUI frontend for the Jujutsu (jj) version
# control system** — companion to the existing _jujutsu binary
# completion in the corpus.  Provides interactive log /
# rebase / squash / split / diff operations in a curses-style
# UI using bubbletea + lipgloss.  Sister to lazygit (existing
# in the corpus) but for jj instead of git, and supports jj's
# revset query language for filtering.
#
# Critical extraction note: jjui uses **Go's standard `flag`
# package** (NOT cobra/argh/cmdr/clap) — continuing the
# corpus's documentation of Go-stdlib-flag CLI patterns from
# R227 ssh-tpm-* and R228 age-plugin-fido2-hmac.  3 of the 7
# unique options have BOTH short and long forms (registered
# via TWO flag calls each):
#   -r / --revset             (main.go:54-55)
#   -p / --period             (main.go:56-57)
#   -n / --limit              (main.go:58-59)
# The remaining 4 are long-only (--version, --config,
# --install-lua-types, --help).
#
# Critical extraction note: 3 flags trigger EARLY-EXIT
# branches at main.go:99-121:
#   --help              prints usage + returns 0
#   --version           prints version + returns 0
#   --install-lua-types writes Lua type defs + returns 0
#   --config            opens config in $EDITOR + returns
#                       config.Edit()'s status
# These do NOT launch the TUI.  All other flags + the
# positional location launch the TUI.  Documented in
# completion descriptions.
#
# Critical extraction note: the `location` positional is
# OPTIONAL — defaults to `os.Getwd()` at main.go:130.  When
# supplied, it's a directory path that contains (or is inside)
# a jj repo (`jj root --color=always` is run to resolve to
# the repo root at line 73).  Completion offers directory
# completion.
#
# Critical extraction note: jjui sets `JJUI=1` in its
# environment (main.go:92) so spawned subprocesses can detect
# they were invoked by jjui.  Useful for `jj` revset condition
# variables that adjust behavior when running under the TUI.
# Documented in the comment block but not surfaced as a
# completable option since it's an env var.

_arguments -s -S \
  '(--help)--help[show help information and exit]' \
  '--version[show jjui version + commit hash and exit]' \
  '(--config)--config[open jjui configuration file in $EDITOR (early-exit; does NOT launch TUI)]' \
  '--install-lua-types[write Lua type definitions to config dir for LuaLS autocomplete (early-exit)]' \
  '(-r --revset)'{-r+,--revset=}'[default revset to display (jj revset syntax, e.g. "all()")]:revset:' \
  '(-p --period)'{-p+,--period=}'[auto-refresh interval in seconds (-1 = default; 0 = disable)]:seconds:' \
  '(-n --limit)'{-n+,--limit=}'[number of revisions to show (default: 0 = all)]:count:' \
  '1:location (jj repo directory; default: CWD):_files -/'
